,Not Recommended,279440,15012712,"Posted: 22 March, 2015",all,raixel,"So I have this game on both Android and PC. The PC version is a terrible port compared to the awesomeness of the mobile game. I actually bought it on mobile after buying the PC version because it looked so great, but on PC it isnt very fun. So I wanted to give it a second chance, and boy I'm glad I did. Its a *great* mobile game, one of my absolute favorite mobile games next to Tales of Illyria. PC, not so much (actually not at all)At least for me, the touchscreen events were almost impossible using a mouse, where on Android they are awesome. It seems that when ported, the devs did nothing to make the quicktime events more mouse friendly. Even on mobile you mess up on occasion, as there isnt much time to do the events. But what becomes fun on a touchscreen is just annoying on a mouse. They expect you to be able to do the same quick tap-drag-circle etc events with the exact same speed and accuracy  with a mouse on PC as with your finger or stylus on a tablet. In short, its frustratingly difficult and ruins the game.Yes, I recommend it on mobile, but a big NO for the PC. Oh, and did I mention its $12.99 on google play instead of $14.99? Get it there, don't waste your time with this terrible PC port."
