76561197986118370,Recommended,279440,24155445,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,Ring of Zen,"I must first declare that the Lone Wolf game books were my one of my fondest childhood pastime.   For this modern remake, the narrative by Joe Dever is much darker compared to the original books but still good storytelling. The illustration and art is impressive too but for me Gary Chalk's work will always define how I see Magnamund.Being a port from a handheld game, the combat mechanics is simple and the fights and enemy variety gets repetitive. The plot is pretty linear and progress is mostly combat rather than plot driven. Nostalgia certainly have biased my review but I am giving it a thumbs up and hoping for sequels. (I sure hope someone would take up the mantle of the late Mr Dever and continue his legacy). Those who are unfamiliar with Lone Wolf may not agree."
76561198116000643,Recommended,279440,31332204,Posted: 23 April,all,Wolfblade,"So i bought this game on a whim thinking that it would be a game that i would play and forget about in a short amount of time, oh how wrong i was. I had never heard of the Lone Wolf adventure stiry before so this game opened up my mind to a whole new world. Having just beaten the game, i will  list what i beleve are the pros and cons of the game for me.Some replayability.Pros:Great Story where your choices do matter.Great Turn-based combat system where your choices right befoer combat can either be advantageous or disadvantageous to you.Creative writing that draws you into the character.Variety of enemies that are unique in their own aspect.QTE's add a bit of a challenge to the game.There are physics for turning the pages, awesome touch to the game that adds character to the game.Intro and outro cutscenes to battle go from story book to animated and vice versa which is just awesome and is exactly how i would imagine characters from a book coming to life.If you are having trouble with the shianti puzles, you can take the health damage and just continue on with your day.Now for the Cons:While the enemies are unique, combat gets boring after awhile if you have to grind (which you do on hard)The Shianti puzzles are an interesting aspect, but are extremely difficult to solve. Also wish there was some more consequences to failing the puzzles other than just health loss, i felt like i was cheating just taking the hp damage at times with no other repercusions.The inventory and crafting system are a little awkward at times.I felt like while upgrading armor and weapons helped a little bit, i would have liked for a more noticable difference between leather Kai armour and Kai plate armour.Overall, i give this game a 9/10 and it has easily made it's way onto my top 10. I for one am going to go look into the rest of the Lone Wolf stories after this.For the Sommerlund and the Kai!"
76561198173241122,Recommended,279440,31492876,Posted: 1 May,all,Sir Hectorio,"I stumbled over this game in a sale and I am absolutely content to have bought and played it.It is kind of a different RPG, which lives through the written narative which unfolds as you play the game.You cant chose a character, you play as the last Kai-Lord (a worshipper of the God Kai, who has bestowed great (magical) powers to his followers) that is left after their monastry has been overrun. Which powers you have you determine in the beginning of the game, there are good tutorials on the character creation so I wont refer to it any further. You have a powerful sword, the Sommerswerd, that is capable of dealing great damage to your foes. Those powers are needed, because you will meet powerful foes aswell and tactic and timing play a good part in fighting.While the main story is written and holds at points where you can make choices to use certain abilities or the way the next fight will take place, your choices have consequences, resulting in advantage or disadvantage, victory or death.Graphics, animated graphics or will loosen up the story. You can navigate to different places on the map, though you dont have much choices, since the story follows a more or less linear story, and you cant go back: the story is devided in 4 acts and you only can move to places you have been before in the same act.Fighting itself is divided in turns according to a fading energy-meter which has to refill to be able to act again. You can chose to use the sommerswerd, sword and shield (or any other weapon you chose), throwing missiles or magic skills which also have a cooldown timer until your action-energy has run out. Again your choices matter in the fight. The fight takes places in an animated 3D fight. Your skills grow in power with more freequent use (and unlock an additional effect).As it seems it is a remake of some gaming series that I didnt know. Although unfamiliar with that background-story, the good storytelling dragged me into the lore and the story. By chance I took a good set of skills (i liked healing, mind over matter, animal kinship and sixth sense, which really can prove helpful in some tasks), and played through the main story in 14-15 hours on a normal difficulty (which proves good to get to know the game-style)Although the story is linear, so there is no great open world, no characters to chose, repeated fighting (once you have your set of skills) and especially a repeating and narrow sound track, I really liked the story and the way it was realized in the game. Having meaningful choices, influencing the gameplay and sometimes the story, resolving minigames and especially finding the right fighting tactics was fun to me and absolutely outweigh the negative points.I really can recommend this games for players that like to dive into a narrative, that like language and reading and solving problems and that are interested in playing a different kind of RPG."
76561198098038197,Recommended,279440,34703702,Posted: 2 September,all,MuadDib80,"As a kid, I read the books by Joe Denver. As an adult, I love the fact that I can relive my childhood memories of the Lone Wolf Books. I want to thank everyone that worked on this project. The story is rich just like I remember it being. The graphics are eye catching and outstanding. The combat system is the only thing that I would say is not quite right. You have the same basic combat moves all the time. I wish that there were more to do but it a very good system that you have.I would tell everyone that has ever wanted to know what a chose your own adventure books can become to pick this game up and learn what it is to be a child again!"
